pudl-migration.title: pudl0038 Historical Photograph Collection: Grounds and Buildings Series

comments.body:
Recent questions from stakeholders:

Is it possible to display the box (and item number, if possible) in one of the metadata fields in the “More information” area? We have this information in the PUDL, it is present in the spreadsheet in the location field, and it would be very helpful to have it in Figgy.  We are open to your suggestions about which metadata field would be available and would work for this.

- Yes, we can and @escowles , I believe, has done this.

Can we change the rights statement for all items to “Copyright not Evaluated” from the current “No Known Copyright.”

- Yes we can

 We had hoped that we could seamlessly scroll through all of the images associated with a component rather than having to click on each individual image, but we realized that this structure might be necessary in order to display the metadata associated with each image—so that is fine if so.

 We would like to move forward with a DPUL exhibition for this collection, but it might make sense to first work on the Historical Postcard Collection exhibit because you have gotten us started with that and it may be less complicated than the photograph collection.

On 09/07/2020, we (re)ingested pudl0038 (AC111) as a collection of multi-volume works based on component id. On 9/14/2020, @kelea99 wrote to Lynn, Alexis, and Ann Marie, telling them of the ingest of the MVWs and asking for their review.

In an email dated December 18, 2020 (subject RE: Grounds and Buildings MVWs and Historic Postcards DPUL test site ready for review), Lynn Durgin responded to @kelea99 's request for an update with the statement @kelea99 quotes above. In particular, she says

>We had hoped that we could seamlessly scroll through all of the images associated with a component rather than having to click on each individual image, but we realized that this structure might be necessary in order to display the metadata associated with each image—so that is fine if so.

This sounds like they would like to abandon the MVW approach and ingest these as single items.  Is that correct, @kelea99 and @escowles ?
Decision 01/19/21: While the stakeholders would like a more seamless experience, they are find with the MVW approach since it allows retaining the metadata for each individual photo.

@cwulfman : create new collection (linked to AC111) and write script to go through all the source_metadata_identifiers (the collection ids in the spreadsheet) and add them to that collection : https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/bd9b272c-fdf6-41a8-baa9-cb4524c777d8
